#C++ Preprocessor
C++ Preprocessor doesn't understand C++ 
It simply follows the preprocessor directives and gets the source code ready for the compiler 
the compiler is the program that does understand C++

#the main() function 
int main (int argc, char* argv[]){
}
program.exe argument1 argument2

#namespaces
name conflict 가능성을 줄이고자 해결하기 위해서 
version
std::cin
using namespace std; // large program에 부적절함. 
using std::cout; // use only what you need 

#cout and <<
insert the data into the cout stream 
cout << data;

can be chained 
cout << "data 1 is " << data1;

#cin and >> 
extract data from the cin stream based on data's type
cin >> data;

can be chained 
cin >> data1 >> data2;

can fail if the entered data cannot be interpreted
data could have an undetermined value. 


cin extraction uses white space that is 
spaces, tabs, new lines as terminating the value being extracted.
if you put spaces between the things that you type in,
the spaces will be ignored.

extract data from the cin stream based on data's type
cin >> data;

can be chained
cin >> data1 >> data2

#declaring and initializing 
data type 을 만들 수 있다
Account franks_account;
Person james;



#variable 
random access memory is a contiguous block of storage. 
메모리 주소에 이름을 붙여 준 것이 variable 

#initializing Variables 
int age; // uninitialized 
int age = 21; // C-like initialization
int age (21); // constructor initialization
int age {21}; // C++ list initilization syntax 

# size and precision of c++'s primitive data types

char exactly one byte. at least 8bits. 
char16_t at least16
char32_t at least 32 

integer types (type name/ size&precision)
signed short at least 16bits. 
signed int at least 16bits
signed long at least 32bits
signed long long at least 64bits. 

unsigned short int at least 16bits. 
unsigned int at least 16bits
unsigned long at least 32bits
unsigned long long at least 64bits. 
*unsigned는 0또는 양수 

type name / size&typical precision / typical Range
float /  &7 decimal digits / 1.2x 10^-38 to 3.4x 10^38
double / no less than float & 15 decimal digits / 2.2x 10^-308 to 1.8x 10^308
long double / no less than double& 19 decimal digits / 3.3x10^-4932 to 1.2x10^4932

리얼 넘버로 파이는 무한 수지만 
computers store an approximation of the real number. 

bool / usually 8 bits true or false(C++ keywords) 


#climits for integer types
#include <climits> 
//defined minimum values 이건 상수! 
CHAR_MIN   CHAR_MAX
INT_MIN
SHRT_MIN
LONG_MIN
LLONG_MIN



#cfloat for floating point types 
#include <cfloat>

예시) int age {21}; 변수의 크기를 측정하려면 
sizeof(age) 또는 sizeof age






